  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solar Panels in Haiti for School and Orphanage</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mercy &amp; Sharing shelters, feeds, educates and provides medical care for 120 orphans in Haiti, half of whom are disabled.  On the campus of Mercy &amp; Sharing Village, our school educates and provides a hot meal every day for 300 students.  By installing more solar panels, we can reduce and nearly eliminate our need for fossil fuels.  A challenge gift has already been made, so your donations will be matched dollar for dollar to enable solar panels to be purchased and installed.</narrative>
  </description>
